Model

* General information

  The Repository model sub-project contains the classes used to describe Orchestra peers/schemas. These classes are meant to be used both in the central repository (to maintain a memory cache...), but also 
on the client side.

* Beans

  All these classes can be exported/imported into basic bean classes which expose all the properties. These beans are usefull to communicate with the DAO layer (ORM tools for examples), for webservices 
messages...


Repository DAO

* General information

  This subproject contains all the DAO API used for the centralized repository

* DAO implementations

  <<IBATIS DAO>>
  This DAO implementation uses a RDBMS to store the data (first test were done with MySQL, will be 
installed on DB2 as soon as we'll have the new database server).

  IBATIS is used to reduce the overhead of JDBC development, all the IBATIS resources files (containing 
objects/relations mappings and queries) are stored in the resources directory tree.

   This implementation will be used by the actual centralized repository for Orchestra.
   
  <<Flat file DAO>>
  This implementation has been developed to: 
  
    * Make it easier to test (without an actual database...)

    * Make it easier to store human-readable Peers definition

  TODO: Document the file format

Repository utils

* General information

  This subproject has been created to include a set of utilities that can make it easier to 
create schemas, mappings...

* Utilities

** Schema Loaders

  The SchemaLoader class must be inhereted by any utility that can load a schema from a database or 
any other source. 

  <<JDBC Loader>>

  The SchemaLoaderJDBC class can be used to create a Schema object from a database connection. This 
  loader will accept filters to select the relations to load on:

      * Catalogs names

      * Schemas names

      * Relations names

  Ir will load the relations, their constraints... Foreign keys will only be loaded if they reference a 
  relation that is also loaded in the schema.


DBGroup projects

  The full list of DBGroup projects managed under Maven can be found on {{{https://dbgrpbuild.cis.upenn.edu/infrastructure/projects/index.htm}this page}}

Some "documentation"

* Datatypes

  In this API datatypes are described using the JDBC standard as described in java.sql.Types. Thus the 
type are stored as an int attribute.

   * To get a type name (from its int value), use the method OrchestraTypesTranslator.typeToString(int). 

   * To get a type int value from its name, use the method OrchestraTypesTranslator.typeFromString(String). 
   
* Lists/deep copies
  
  The choice has been made to return the actual inner lists when a method such as getFields is called 
(instead of returning a deep copy to avoid exterior/uncontrolled changes of these lists). This is only 
to improve perfomance and can be changed anytime.
